<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-883-188  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 883 188.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Nov 13 1989 v6 n45 p16(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VMS-compatible mail offers spell checking, editing capabilities.andO;(Gold-Mail, from Data Processing Design Inc.) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schild, Karen.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Data Processing Design Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Gold-Mail (electronic mail system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Electronic Mail SystemsProduct IntroductionCommunications Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>VMS-Compatible Mail Offers Spell Checking, Editing CapabilitiesandM;ANAHEIM, Calif.andP;  -- Data Processing Design has announced a VMS-compatibleE-mail system.andM;Gold-Mail is sold with single-user licenses of Word-11 version 4.3, whichallows users to edit and spell-check messages.andM;The Gold-Mail menu offers mail, read, move, copy, delete, mark, quit, exitand help functions.andP;  Gold-Mail commands are initiated with gold keys, such asGold C to create a message and Gold Q to exit.andM;Gold-Mail lets users underline, center, use boldface or boxes, and createcolumns.andP;  The system also lets users edit the header.andP;  If a user forgets toput a name in the distribution list, for example, he can go back and add thename while writing the message.andM;Messages can be programmed to be sent at a specific time and date.andP;  Deletedmessages can also be undeleted.andM;Another feature, Registered Mail, lets users know if a message has been readby the recipient.andP;  All messages appear in both Gold-Mail and VMS.andM;Data Processing Design plans to add the ability to transfer graphics over VMSmail within six months of Gold-Mail's release, according to companyofficials.andM;Gold-Mail will be available by the end of the year.andP;  Prices will range from$1,900 for a MicroVAX to $3,500 for high-end systems.andM;Data Processing Design Inc. is located at 1400 N. Brasher St., Anaheim, CA92807-2001, (714) 970-1515.andO;</TEXT></DOC>